[The East Penn School District is a public school district located in Lehigh County, Pennsylvania, that operates one high school (Emmaus High School), 2 middle schools (Lower Macungie and Eyer middle schools), and 7 elementary schools (Shoemaker, Macungie, Alburtis, Jefferson, Lincoln, Wescosville, and Willow Lane) in the Lehigh Valley region of eastern Pennsylvania (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Penn_School_District). A map showing the location of the East Penn School District can be seen at https://www.google.com/maps/place/East+Penn+School+District,+PA.

The Lehigh Valley (also known as the Allentown-Bethlehem-Easton, PA-NJ Metropolitan Statistical Area) consists of Carbon, Lehigh, and Northampton counties in eastern Pennsylvania and Warren county on the western edge of New Jersey (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lehigh_Valley). - Mod.ML]

