[Yellowknife, on the northern shore of Great Slave Lake, about 400 km (250 mi) south of the Arctic Circle, is the capital and only city, as well as the largest community, in the Northwest Territories (NWT), Canada (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yellowknife). The Tlicho, also known as the Dogrib, are a Dene First Nations people living in 6 settlements in the NWT (Behchoko, population 2227 residents; Whati, population 522 residents; Gameti, population 291 residents; Wekweeti, population 136 residents; Dettah, population 245 residents; and Ndilo, population 2007 residents. Ndilo is located on the edge of Yellowknife (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ndilo). A map showing the location of these Tlicho communities can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tlicho#Communities. - Mod.ML]
